<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/65270290-lili"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1634655661i/65270290._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/65270290-lili">Lili</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">No, it gives a solid conclusion that doesn&apos;t require the second book. Most people I know that have read it, only read the first one. <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">No, it gives a solid conclusion that doesn't require the second book. Most people I know that have read it, only read the first one. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
