  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_121050628" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/121050628" />
    <a title="Bloody Brilliant Books" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4103031-bloody-brilliant-books"><img alt="Bloody Brilliant Books" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1467323662p2/4103031.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/121050628?book_show_action=true">Sep 10, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bloody Brilliant Books" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bloody Brilliant Books" href="/user/show/4103031-bloody-brilliant-books">Bloody Brilliant Books</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780747587743" href="/book/show/3217299-the-declaration">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4103031-bloody-brilliant-books?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer121050628" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5837951249937709687">The Declaration is one of those stories which in my opinion don’t get enough publicity. Its both eye opening, and heart warming story. It tells the story of Anna, who is a surplus. Surpluses are children which the world has no room for as they’ve developed a anti-mortality drug. Anna lives in Grange Hall with other surpluses, where she is trained to be “useful” and a “good asset” which to Anna means that she’ll be able to make up for the crime of being born.<br/><br/>Children are a rarity in this world as</span>
  <span id="freeText5837951249937709687" style="display:none">The Declaration is one of those stories which in my opinion don’t get enough publicity. Its both eye opening, and heart warming story. It tells the story of Anna, who is a surplus. Surpluses are children which the world has no room for as they’ve developed a anti-mortality drug. Anna lives in Grange Hall with other surpluses, where she is trained to be “useful” and a “good asset” which to Anna means that she’ll be able to make up for the crime of being born.<br /><br />Children are a rarity in this world as when people first take the drug “Longevity”, which provides longevity, they sign a declaration to say they will not have children. Only those who opt out can have children legally and very few opt out, unfortunately for Anna her parents don’t opt out, so Anna was taken away from them when she was just a baby.<br /><br />Grange Hall is a barbaric place where the children are brain washed into thinking their worthless. However when Peter arrives, he start to ask Anna questions which question what has been drilled into since the day she was born.<br /><br />It’s rarely that you find a novel that changes the way you see things but I think that this novel does just this. It changes the way you think of living forever as, you are subliminally faced with the question, “Would you give up your right to children, in exchange for the chance to live forever?” It focuses on Anna but you get a scene of a much wider picture. It raises many ethical issues, but remains a story of a girls fight for freedom. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="5837951249937709687" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

